title: How have waiting times after an urgent referral changed?
analysis_commentary: The percentage of people being seen within two weeks had remained largely consistent, between 95% and 96%, since Quarter 4 2008/09. However, since Quarter 3 2013/14 this has decreased and was at an all-time low of 93.5% in Quarter 1 2014/15.
